               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Javāhir-i khamsah by Shaykh Muḥammad Ghaws̲ Gavālyārī</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2001009476 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_81B-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656451.0x000001 viaf_19540626">Shaykh Muḥammad Ghaws̲ Gavālyārī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656451.0x000001 viaf_19540626">شيخ محمّد غوث گواليارى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21953">Javāhir-i khamsah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21953">جواهر خمسه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Extensive treatise on esoteric aspects of Sufism and the occult sciences by <persName key="viaf_19540626" role="aut">Shaykh Muḥammad Ghaws̲ Gavālyārī</persName>, or Muḥammad ibn Khaṭīr al-Dīn ibn Laṭīf ibn Muʿīn al-Dīn Qattāl ibn Khaṭīr al-Dīn ibn Bāyazīd ibn Khvājah Farīd al-Dīn Nayshāpūrī ʿAṭṭār (d. 970/1562), the latter descends from the Ismāʿīlī imams after <persName key="viaf_100648969" role="oth">Imām Jaʿfar al-Ṣādiq</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The author wrote the work at the age of fifty, in 956/1549. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. Dateable to the late sixteenth century. 
</p>
                        <p>Replacement folios 1-10, 199-201, at the very least. 
</p>
                        <p>Note at the beginning (f. 1r) confirms the folio count as 204. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotated and corrected, occasionally densely, in margins and interlinear spaces by the scribe and many later hands. 
</p>
                        <p>Diagrams on folios 174v, 176r, 179r, 189v-190r. 
</p>
                        <p>Stamped foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Binding, red half leather IOL covers, stamp dated 27 Sep 1916. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios cut and remounted with new margins and rebound; severely cropped, gauze overlay, water stains, creases, wormholes, later repairs. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
